{"key":"processedPost-12947856","value":{"id":12947856,"first":12945217,"last":12948744,"when":1280029869,"utime":"07/25/10 06:51 AM","content":"Fresh air is the number one pinning trigger and you won't get fresh air through polyfill.&nbsp; Remove it and then mist to keep the substrate from drying out.<br />How far above the tub is your light?&nbsp; If it's 12\" above the substrate, you can get four times the amount of light by moving it to 6\" above the substrate.&nbsp; You want your light as close as you can without heating up and/or drying out the substrate.<br />Don't dunk a substrate that has the correct amount of weight.&nbsp; If it's light, soak it.&nbsp; A too wet substrate will perform as poorly as a too dry one.<br />RR","title":"Re: One Mushroom Monotub"}}